reviewText: This collection of Four movies is a nice addition to any movie library.1. Richard Burton and Clint Eastwood star in a Nazi Germany Action Thriller. You'll love it!2. Eastwood. Savalas, Southerland and Rickles in a WWII action comedy, about a few soldiers getting together to steal a bank full of Nazi Gold.3. Eastwood stars again as a piolet going behind Russian Lines to steal a newly developed warplane that could evade radar.4. Eastwood stars as a "By the Book Lifer". on his last tour of duty, Marine Squad Leader in an 1983 invasion of Granada. Avtion with some comedy. A great flick.
summary: You can't go wrong with Eastwood!

reviewText: Now if you were only going to buy one collection as a gift or you were short on space in your library then this would have to be the must have collection. Then of course if you could squeeze in another Clint Eastwood Collection I would go with at least two western collections. I have my own favorites but you could select what you think you would like to see from time to time. I mean in  the war pictures that he was involved in there is one that stands out! It is "Where Eagles Dare." That one has Richard Burton. The scenery is out of this world. Quite a good story too! I mean you could probably dump some other movies to make more room for movies by Clint Eastwood. Firefox in this collection is a real classic! I love it! Then Heartbreak Ridge is unmistakably a great movie of a Marine who has been in more campaigns then Carter has liver pills!  If you are a follower of Clint Eastwood you will notice that all his movies have on phrase that is repeated over and over. Like in Magnum Force we hear, "Go ahead make my day!" So after saying that there is nothing more to say.
